{"_id":"N2v8Qst0p5gfQczU","name":"Cleansing Slate","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/tablet-stone-grey-pink.webp","system":{"description":"As a reaction to being affected by either the poisoned or disoriented condition, you may cleanse yourself of both of those conditions.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"reaction","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"The dull, featureless gray relieves the disarray of pitched combat when placed at the body's meridians.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":80000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hD2f0sUyjaZh8bZU","name":"Flippermorph Treads","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/feet/boots-collared-blue.webp","system":{"description":"As a Use Item action, you may enable or disable this item. While enabled and equipped, your Speed is reduced by 5 feet and you gain basic Swimming mobility.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"A seemingly ordinary pair of boots that, when you click their heels, can transform into some diving flippers.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":81000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"gR603k1OfXEGwHdD","name":"Fractured Agate","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/gems/gem-faceted-cushion-teal-black.webp","system":{"description":"As a reaction immediately after you make a damage roll, you may choose some of the dice rolled and replace their outcome with their maximum value before the damage is dealt. The number of dice chosen is equal to half your Tier Bonus.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"reaction","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"Insult to injury crystallized within the break lines of its wavy hues.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":82000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"CP0WSQ2JfnoF5zUd","name":"Lucid Spectacles","type":"curio","img":"icons/tools/scribal/spectacles-glasses.webp","system":{"description":"While equipped, you gain advantage on Search checks.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"It's not that the distracting details aren't there, it is that you simply see them for what they are.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":83000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"WtS8ZPZC6q3niKdh","name":"The S-Cape","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/back/cape-layered-blue-accent.webp","system":{"description":"While equipped, you gain advantage on Escape checks.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"It stands for Slippery.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":84000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"k06eyzSAjmIwNlxD","name":"Warding Quartz","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/stone/stone-white-quartz-ball.webp","system":{"description":"Multiple variants of **Warding Quartz** exist for the following damage types: **acid**, **cold**, **fire**, **force**, **lightning**, **necrotic**, **poison**, **psychic**, and **radiant**.\n\nAs a reaction when you are dealt damage of this variant's type, you may gain a DB against that damage type equal to 5 - half your Tier Bonus until the end of the current turn.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"reaction","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"The angles of the cut are perfectly positioned to absorb and deflect.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":85000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"sPlUnW5cLA1rk5s6","name":"Apacknid","type":"curio","img":"icons/containers/bags/pack-leather-brown.webp","system":{"description":"As a Use Item action, you may either **Deploy** this item or, once per long rest, **Climb** with it:\n\n* **Deploy.** The item is *deployed* onto a target unoccupied space within 10 feet of you, leaping off of your back with all objects stowed in it and gaining advanced Climbing mobility. Once during each of your turns you may direct the deployed item to travel up to 30 feet. A Pick Up action on this item causes it to no longer be deployed.\n\n* **Climb.** You cause the item to grant its wearer advanced Climbing mobility for 10 minutes.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"A handy backpack with retractable spider legs able to carry your stuff and just strong enough to lift you with it.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":86000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"dC9VS18rSFbnE5nD","name":"Carnelian Rose","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/gems/gem-rough-round-pink.webp","system":{"description":"Multiple variants of **Carnelian Rose** exist for the following ability modifiers: **INT**, **WIS**, and **CHA**.\n\nOnce per rest, as a reaction when making an attack check that does not use this variant's ability modifier, you may add this variant's ability modifier to the total.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"reaction","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"A bold statement, and fortune favors the bold.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":87000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"o32Lcgn39N38oCtb","name":"Championship Belt","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/waist/belt-buckle-gold-blue.webp","system":{"description":"While equipped, you gain advantage on Grapple and Pin checks.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"A weighted belt with a massive golden emblem placed at the center. Each victory claimed by the owner etches a tally mark in the medallion.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":88000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XxxOINyAF9MgvIQ4","name":"Hopeful Opal","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/gems/pearl-water.webp","system":{"description":"Multiple variants of **Hopeful Opal** exist for the following saving throw types: **Poise**, **Reflex**, **Fortitude**, **Quick-Wits**, **Will**, and **Courage**.\n\nAs a reaction when you make a saving throw of this variant's type, you may add 1d4 to the total.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"reaction","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"Endless possibilities twinkle within the scintillating stone.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":89000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"0y1JTG4Y3TlP6bYz","name":"Intrusive Chime","type":"curio","img":"icons/tools/instruments/chimes-wood-brown.webp","system":{"description":"Once per rest, you may cast **Never Mind** at 1st Circle using your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"The pleasant ringing serves as an immediate distraction from whatever blunder you just blurted out.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":90000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"GNK5oozcSlpy2CbL","name":"Phantom Strides","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/feet/boots-collared-leather-grey.webp","system":{"description":"While equipped, you gain advantage on Vanish checks.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"A gloomy mist swirls around the soles. You tread with no more than a whisper of a footfall.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":91000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"1ADnmwOQYUoAsi17","name":"Clouded Diamond","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/gems/gem-faceted-diamond-pink.webp","system":{"description":"Once per rest, you may cast **Double Jump** at 2nd Circle using your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"Originally mistaken for a hailstone, this gem now turns you into one.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":92000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"VX3FyuRBRsaBufiR","name":"Geminid Gem","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/finger/ring-band-studded-gold-blue.webp","system":{"description":"This item is paired with another **Geminid Gem**. Purchasing or crafting this item creates a copy that is paired to this one.\n\nOnce per long rest, either of the wearers may take a reaction at any point to cast **Translocate** at 2nd Circle using their INT, WIS, or CHA as their spellcasting modifier. The caster must target the other wearer.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"reaction","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"A pair of rings with a penchant for trading their wearers.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":93000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XAum6MkpsVpIf1hX","name":"Rocket Boots","type":"curio","img":"icons/skills/movement/feet-winged-boots-blue.webp","system":{"description":"As a Use Item action once per long rest, you may cause the item to grant its wearer basic Hovering mobility for 10 minutes.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"The wings attached on the sides are really just fins. It propels more than it flies.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":94000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"eRukTemY2x5BvZDo","name":"Snowglint Sapphire","type":"curio","img":"icons/magic/water/snowflake-ice-blue.webp","system":{"description":"As a reaction to being affected by either the slowed or frozen condition, you may cleanse yourself of both of those conditions and inflict them on a target creature within 15 feet of you until the end of their next turn.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"reaction","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"Set within a silver snowflake, this gem glistens with winter energy.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":95000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"W1T8fDaRJGJBKUcw","name":"Solemn Timepiece","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/tech/watch.webp","system":{"description":"While equipped, you gain advantage on Initiate checks.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"A wristwatch hums with the perpetuity of procession. Not a moment has gone by without it all falling exactly into place. Not a word need be shared as everything and everyone takes their cue.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":96000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ItVvfT2FXCoUDNlT","name":"Cloudwing Cloak","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/back/cloak-collared-blue.webp","system":{"description":"While equipped, you gain basic Flying mobility.","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"A cloak woven from vaporous threading. Light as a feather, you soar through the sky.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":97000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"yP0NOvlrx4vEMdvf","name":"Schism Pearl","type":"curio","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-slit-pink.webp","system":{"description":"As a reaction when making an attack check, you may reduce the target's AC to their Base AC for that attack check.","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"reaction","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"The fissure encased within blinks like a cat's eye, seeing through every ruse with piercing insight.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":98000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"DjfPrBHMo2MyXq4Q","name":"Spellbreaker Bead","type":"curio","img":"icons/magic/unholy/orb-hands-pink.webp","system":{"description":"As a reaction, you may cast **Counterspell** at 2nd Circle using your CON as your spellcasting modifier. When you cast **Counterspell** using this item, you deal **5 injuring force damage** to yourself. This damage roll is cumulatively doubled after each use of this item, but it is reset to 5 at the end of your next long rest.","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"reaction","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"A finely polished blood stone compressed by the weight of pure magic.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":99000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"e8WplnrCCscCNfmN","name":"Spirited Peridot","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/gems/gem-faceted-diamond-green.webp","system":{"description":"As a reaction when you are about to burn a Resolve, you may instead use this item to gain the effects of burning a Resolve. This item cannot be used again until you succeed a DC 15 flat check, which you may attempt once at the end of each long rest.\n\n# **List of Battlesmith Items**","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Artisan","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"reaction","mainType":"Wearable","subType":"","flavor":"Glittering with the spark of life, the moss suspended in the verdant stone seeps with eternal vigor.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ceg9xMb8eMTRnhK6","name":"Firebreath Weapon","type":"curio","img":"icons/creatures/abilities/dragon-fire-breath-orange.webp","system":{"description":"This item can be purposed for any fighting style. This weapon has the following trait and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the trait with a minor reforge trait of your choice.\n\n* **Energized (Pyral).** When you hit with a weapon attack using this item, you may convert all of the attack's damage to **fire damage**.\n\nOnce per long rest, after you make a weapon attack with this item, you may take a Use Item action to cause all creatures and objects within a 10 foot cone in front of you to make a basic **Reflex** saving throw to resist **fire damage**.\n\nThe saving throw's DC and the damage dealt is based on the item's rarity:\n\n* **Common**. DC 14 against **2d8 fire damage**.\n\n* **Uncommon**. DC 17 against **4d8 fire damage**.\n\n* **Rare**. DC 20 against **6d8 fire damage.**\n\n* **Legendary**. DC 23 against **8d8 fire damage.**","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Weapon","subType":"","flavor":"Its metal is alloyed with gold stolen from a dragon's hoard. Its fury rests without slumber.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":101000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"D1CLCKrMlqwwu2cv","name":"Folding Armor","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-banded-steel-studded.webp","system":{"description":"This armor may be any type of armor. This armor has the following trait and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the trait with a minor reforge trait of your choice.\n\n* **Shock-Absorbing.** When you are dealt falling damage, you may halve the damage taken.\n\nAs a Use Item action, you may immediately take off or wear this armor. If you take off this armor and are holding a different armor with the **Quick Collapse** aspect, you may wear that armor as part of the same Use Item action.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Armor","subType":"","flavor":"A finely-tuned system of interlocking plates that swiftly collapses into a compact form. Despite this intricacy, it is anything but delicate.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":102000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zShEHYtSIzSQqGor","name":"Hoarfrost Shield","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-crystal-blue.webp","system":{"description":"This shield has the following trait and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the trait with a minor reforge trait of your choice.\n\n* **Spiked.** In addition to being a shield, this item also counts as a weapon suitable for throwing, usable for any fighting style that does not have the **Exclusive** trait. You may apply weapon reforge traits and weapon aspects to this item.\n\nOnce per long rest, after taking the Raise Shield action using this item, you may take a Use Item action to cause all spaces within 15 feet of you to act as difficult terrain until the start of your next turn.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"Raise Shield action","mainType":"Shield","subType":"","flavor":"Clawing icicles are emblazoned upon the shield, projecting outward an eternal chill. You form the boundary between where life ends and where winter begins.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":103000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"geOhXD0dV3gObRIN","name":"Mutate Plate","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-collared-steel-green.webp","system":{"description":"This armor may be any type of armor. This armor has the following trait and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the trait with a minor reforge trait of your choice.\n\n* **Triumphant.** You do not fall prone from burning a Resolve.\n\nAs a Use Item action, you may gain a DB against a **physical damage** type of your choosing until the start of your next turn or you use **Ironweave** again. The DB's amount depends on this item's rarity (5 for Common, 10 for Uncommon, 15 for Rare, and 20 for Legendary).","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Armor","subType":"","flavor":"If you know the enemy and know yourself, you need not fear the result of a hundred battles.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":104000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"OSgLi6CRxbRXFpH9","name":"Windfury Blade","type":"curio","img":"icons/weapons/swords/greatsword-crossguard-blue.webp","system":{"description":"This item can be purposed for any fighting style. This weapon has the following trait and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the trait with a minor reforge trait of your choice.\n\n* **Returning.** You may perform a one minute ritual to *bind* this item to you. This item may be bound to only one creature. When you take the Retrieve object interaction, you may instead teleport a bound item to you and then hold it.\n\nOnce per long rest, as a Use Item action, you may travel up to your Speed and then make a light weapon attack with this item.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Weapon","subType":"","flavor":"Carved into it is the storied legacy of stormclouds. With every strike it shall not be forgotten.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":105000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"rB1eNWzw5zTi4z6e","name":"Author's Plume","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/materials/feather-red.webp","system":{"description":"This item can be purposed for any fighting style. This weapon has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with minor reforge traits of your choice.\n\n* **Attuned.** In addition to being a weapon, this item also counts as a spellcasting focus. You may apply spellcasting focus aspects to this item.\n\n* **Energized (Ethereal).** When you hit with a weapon attack using this item, you may convert all of the attack's damage to **force damage**.\n\nOnce per long rest, after you make a weapon attack with this item, you may take a Use Item action to teleport yourself and this item to a target unoccupied space within 30 feet of you. If the weapon attack hit, you may also cause the target of the attack to make a **Poise** saving throw. On a failure, the target is teleported with you.\n\nThe saving throw DC depends on the item's rarity (14 for Common, 17 for Uncommon, 20 for Rare, and 23 for Legendary).","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Weapon","subType":"","flavor":"A pinion of the pen that wrote upon the page of the world.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":106000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"GBM2fZJoUKLs0nZc","name":"Forceglass Bulwark","type":"curio","img":"icons/magic/defensive/shield-barrier-blue.webp","system":{"description":"This shield has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with two minor reforge traits of your choice.\n\n* **Steady (Tower).** While you gain the benefits of the Raise Shield action or Reactive Block reaction using this item, you gain advantage on saving throws made to resist falling prone.\n* **Thunderous.** When you take the Reactive Block reaction using this item against a melee attack and it misses, the attacker incurs disadvantage on the next attack they make this turn.\n\nAs a Use Item action once per long rest, you may drop this item to *project* it and form a 25 foot long, 15 foot high rectangular wall originating in front of you that persists while this item is projected. The wall has a Toughness of 20 and HP based on this item's rarity (10 for Common, 20 for Uncommon, 30 for Rare, and 40 for Legendary). If the wall is destroyed, the effect ends and the shield returns to its original form, dropping onto the ground.\n\nWhile projected, this item cannot be used as a shield and, if the wall is within your Reach, you may take a Use Item action to end the effect early and hold the shield once more. Only the creature that projected this item may end the effect early in this manner.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Shield","subType":"","flavor":"A panel of arcane energies condensed into a wavy glass. A special conduit resides within the handle to regulate the size and shape of the projected solid.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":107000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"bD1b9f0PRV20pPlp","name":"Honeysuckle Hauberk","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-scale-leather.webp","system":{"description":"This armor may be any type of armor. This armor has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with two minor reforge traits of your choice.\n\n* **Resistant (Curative).** You gain a DB against **poison damage** based on the rarity of the item: 5, 10, 15, and 20 for Common, Uncommon, Rare, and Legendary respectively.\n\n* **Mobile (Stabilized).** You gain basic Climbing mobility.\n\nAs a Use Item action once per long rest, you may cleanse yourself of the poisoned condition and **regain ST**. The ST regained depends on the item's rarity (4d6 for Common, 8d6 for Uncommon, 12d6 for Rare, and 16d6 for Legendary).","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Armor","subType":"","flavor":"A gnarled mass of symbiotic foliage formed into a piece of living armor. As a substitute for chain mail, movement can be a little stiff but it helps the most where it counts.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":108000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"umE3hs0Tqw8TR31f","name":"Lightning Chakram","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/shield/buckler-wooden-boss-lightning.webp","system":{"description":"This item can be purposed for any fighting style and is suitable for throwing. This weapon has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with minor reforge traits of your choice.\n\n* **Energized (Electric).** When you hit with a weapon attack using this item, you may convert all of the attack's damage to **lightning damage**.\n\n* **Returning.** You may perform a one minute ritual to *bind* this item to you. This item may be bound to only one creature. When you take the Retrieve object interaction, you may instead teleport a bound item to you and then hold it.\n\nOnce per long rest, after you make a weapon attack with this item against a target within 10 feet of you, you may take a Use Item action to cause all creatures of your choice within 10 feet of you to make a basic **Poise** saving throw to resist **lightning damage**. On a failure, an affected creature is also pulled 5 feet closer to you to an unoccupied space.\n\nThe saving throw's DC and the damage dealt is based on the item's rarity:\n\n* **Common**. DC 14 against **2d8 lightning damage**.\n\n* **Uncommon**. DC 17 against **4d8 lightning damage**.\n\n* **Rare**. DC 20 against **6d8 lightning damage.**\n\n* **Legendary**. DC 23 against **8d8 lightning damage.**","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Retrieve object interaction","mainType":"Weapon","subType":"","flavor":"A coil of scintillating wire bound with magnetic spines, eager to encircle and electrify.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":109000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"DkqibnHm8vTjkHau","name":"Sea Serpent Cuirass","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-cuirass-steel-blue.webp","system":{"description":"This armor may be any type of armor. This armor has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with two minor reforge traits of your choice.\n\n* **Finned.** You gain basic Swimming mobility.\n\n* **Resistant (Shimmering).** You gain a DB against **radiant damage** based on the rarity of the item: 5, 10, 15, and 20 for Common, Uncommon, Rare, and Legendary respectively.\n\nAs a Use Item action once per long rest, you may cause all creatures of your choosing within 10 feet of you to make a **Poise** saving throw. The DC of the saving throw depends on the rarity of the item (14 for Common, 17 for Uncommon, 20 for Rare, and 23 for Legendary). On a failure, an affected creature is pushed 10 feet away from you.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Armor","subType":"","flavor":"The shifting hues of the scales form an animate image of a stormy sea. As you call upon its magic, lightning crackles in the backdrop.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":110000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"TfQ0lzrP5Um5lM62","name":"Bullseye Buckler","type":"curio","img":"icons/skills/ranged/target-bullseye-arrow-yellow.webp","system":{"description":"This shield has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with reforge traits of your choice of at most one major reforge trait.\n\n* **Steady (Bold).** While you gain the benefits of the Raise Shield action or Reactive Block reaction using this item, you gain advantage on saving throws made to resist being frightened.\n* **Thunderous.** When you take the Reactive Block reaction using this item against a melee attack and it misses, the attacker incurs disadvantage on the next attack they make this turn.\n* **Stalwart (Elusive).** While you gain the benefits of the Raise Shield action or Reactive Block reaction using this item, you gain advantage on **Reflex** saving throws.\n\nAs a reaction once per long rest, if you are within 15 of a ranged attack's targeting path, you may cause the attack to target you instead and gain the benefits of the Reactive Block reaction against the attack.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"reaction","mainType":"Shield","subType":"","flavor":"It's got big red circles painted on it - of course they're going to aim for it.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":111000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"0jrd59KZTTGqY1H4","name":"Forgebound Plating","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-banded-steel-gold.webp","system":{"description":"This armor is Fortified armor. This armor has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with reforge traits of your choice of at most one major reforge trait.\n\n* **Resistant (Hearthwrought).** You gain a DB against **fire damage** based on the rarity of the item: 5, 10, 15, and 20 for Common, Uncommon, Rare, and Legendary respectively.\n\n* **Triumphant.** You do not fall prone from burning a Resolve.\n\n* **Anchored.** You cannot be pushed or pulled.\n\nAs a Use Item action once per long rest, you may gain the following benefits for 10 minutes or until your ST breaks or you expend a Resolve:\n\n* **Enwreathed.** If this armor has the **Resistant** reforge trait, its DB is doubled and creatures and objects other than you within 5 feet of you for the first time since your most recent turn are dealt damage of the same type as resisted by the **Resistant** reforge trait. The damage dealt depends on the item's rarity (5 for Common, 10 for Uncommon, 15 for Rare, and 20 for Legendary).\n\n* **Welded.** Creatures you have grappled incur disadvantage on Escape checks.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Armor","subType":"Fortified","flavor":"A suit of armor drawn from tempered slag forged in magma. Trapped within is a volcanic might few can claim to best.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":112000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"4zIXCYHh7vBR3QCr","name":"Skyrunner Wraps","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/chest/robe-layered-white.webp","system":{"description":"This armor is Agile armor. This armor has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with reforge traits of your choice of at most one major reforge trait.\n\n* **Mobile (Springed).** You gain basic Jumping mobility.\n\n* **Shock-Absorbing.** When you are dealt falling damage, you may halve the damage taken.\n\n* **Swift.** Your Speed is increased by 10 feet.\n\nAs a Use Item action once per long rest, you may gain advanced Hovering mobility then travel up to your Speed. This Hovering mobility persists until either the end of your next turn or you move again, and all ranged attacks against you automatically miss while you have this Hovering mobility.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Armor","subType":"Agile","flavor":"Tough bandages that, while firm, keep a loose grip on your skin. Shrill winds circle around as you leap through the air.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":113000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"k8EXkR8stvVQQhNC","name":"Truthbearer","type":"curio","img":"icons/skills/targeting/target-glowing-yellow.webp","system":{"description":"This item can be purposed for any fighting style. This weapon has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with minor reforge traits and up to one major reforge trait of your choice.\n\n* **Energized (Sunlit).** When you hit with a weapon attack using this item, you may convert all of the attack's damage to **radiant damage**.\n\n* **Returning.** You may perform a one minute ritual to *bind* this item to you. This item may be bound to only one creature. When you take the Retrieve object interaction, you may instead teleport a bound item to you and then hold it.\n\n* **Keen.** The critical hit threshold of weapon attacks made with this item is reduced by 1\\.\n\nOnce per long rest, after you make a weapon attack with this item, you may take a Use Item action to cause the target of the attack to make a basic **Reflex** saving throw to resist **radiant damage**. On a failure, an affected subject may not gain the benefits of the invisible condition and all illusions they create or have created become obvious for the next 10 minutes.\n\nThe saving throw's DC and the damage dealt is based on the item's rarity:\n\n* **Common**. DC 14 against **2d12 radiant damage**.\n\n* **Uncommon**. DC 17 against **4d12 radiant damage**.\n\n* **Rare**. DC 20 against **6d12 radiant damage.**\n\n* **Legendary**. DC 23 against **8d12 radiant damage.**","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Retrieve object interaction","mainType":"Weapon","subType":"","flavor":"A trusted battering ram against which no fortress of deceit may hold. Even amidst pitch darkness it carries the glint of the morning sun.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":114000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XdwsfnSGhziUyTNC","name":"Winterwing Bow","type":"curio","img":"icons/weapons/bows/shortbow-recurve-blue.webp","system":{"description":"This weapon is purposed for either the Basic Ranged or Loading Ranged fighting styles. This weapon has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with minor reforge traits and up to one major reforge trait of your choice.\n\n* **Attuned.** In addition to being a weapon, this item also counts as a spellcasting focus. You may apply spellcasting focus aspects to this item.\n\n* **Energized (Frigid).** When you hit with a weapon attack using this item, you may convert all of the attack's damage to **cold damage**.\n\n* **Seeking.** When you hit with a weapon attack using this item, the target's AC is reduced by one guard step until the end of the current turn (they may either have their Full Guard AC, Half Guard AC, or Base AC).\n\nOnce per long rest, after you make a weapon attack with this item, you may take a Use Item action to cause the target of the attack and all creatures and objects within 10 feet of it to make a basic **Reflex** saving throw to resist **cold damage**. On a failure, an affected creature is slowed until the end of their next turn.\n\nThe saving throw's DC and the damage dealt is based on the item's rarity:\n\n* **Common**. DC 14 against **2d8 cold damage**.\n\n* **Uncommon**. DC 17 against **4d8 cold damage**.\n\n* **Rare**. DC 20 against **6d8 cold damage.**\n\n* **Legendary**. DC 23 against **8d8 cold damage.**","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Weapon","subType":"","flavor":"A bow blessed by a boreal phoenix in both its grace and ferocity.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":115000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"PQY8FKSbOnr9h6ur","name":"Abyssal Veil","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/back/cloak-collared-purple-gold.webp","system":{"description":"This armor may be any type of armor. This armor has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with reforge traits of your choice of at most two major reforge traits.\n\n* **Resistant (Soulful).** You gain a DB against **necrotic** damage based on the rarity of the item: 5, 10, 15, and 20 for Common, Uncommon, Rare, and Legendary respectively.\n\n* **Triumphant.** You do not fall prone from burning a Resolve.\n\n* **Adamantine.** Critical hits scored against you instead count as normal hits.\n\n* **Anchored.** You cannot be pushed or pulled.\n\nWhen you burn a Resolve while equipped, this item gains one *abyssal charge* that remains until used or until you take a Refresh downtime activity. As a Use Item action, you may expend an abyssal charge from the item to cause a target creature within 60 feet of you to make a basic **Will** saving throw to resist **necrotic damage**. On a failure, an affected creature is incapacitated until the end of its next turn. The saving throw's DC and the damage dealt is based on the item's rarity:\n\n* **Common**. DC 14 against **3d8 necrotic damage**.\n\n* **Uncommon**. DC 17 against **6d8 necrotic damage**.\n\n* **Rare**. DC 20 against **9d8 necrotic damage.**\n\n* **Legendary**. DC 23 against **12d8 necrotic damage.**","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Armor","subType":"","flavor":"A dreadful set of armor that weighs heavier with each defiance of the inevitable. As ghastly demise concentrates in the palm of your hand, you know it is never without cost.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":116000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ATfvYMqJnQ7tUoWX","name":"Calcified Dread","type":"curio","img":"icons/weapons/daggers/dagger-bone-black.webp","system":{"description":"This weapon can be purposed for any fighting style. This weapon has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with minor reforge traits and up to two major reforge traits of your choice.\n\n* **Disguised.** You may determine a *disguised form* for the item, which may be any ordinary object of roughly the same Size and shape. For example, you could designate the disguised form of a sword to be a cane. While equipped, you may take an object interaction to cause this item to either transform into its disguised form or return it to its original form.\n\n* **Energized (Illusory).** When you hit with a weapon attack using this item, you may convert all of the attack's damage to **psychic damage**.\n\n* **Seeking.** When you hit with a weapon attack using this item, the target's AC is reduced by one guard step until the end of the current turn (they may either have their Full Guard AC, Half Guard AC, or Base AC).\n\n* **Spectral.** When you make weapon attacks using this item, the targeting path does not need to be unobstructed.\n\nOnce per long rest, after you make a weapon attack with this item, you may take a Use Item action to cause the target of the attack to make a **Quick-Wits** saving throw. On a failure, the target is *distressed* for 10 minutes. When a creature distressed by this aspect targets you, your occupied space, or your location, they are dealt **psychic damage** and afterwards becomes disoriented until the end of the current turn.\n\nThe saving throw's DC and the damage dealt is based on the item's rarity:\n\n* **Common**. DC 14 against **2d6 psychic damage**.\n\n* **Uncommon**. DC 17 against **4d6 psychic damage**.\n\n* **Rare**. DC 20 against **6d6 psychic damage.**\n\n* **Legendary**. DC 23 against **8d6 psychic damage.**","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"object interaction","mainType":"Weapon","subType":"","flavor":"A lingering thought made manifest as a spindling dagger burying deeper and deeper into the nightmares of your foes.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":117000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"LFgzGLKolLiBxe7O","name":"Dream Ward","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/dreamcatcher-blue.webp","system":{"description":"This shield has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with reforge traits of your choice of at most one major reforge trait.\n\n* **Spiked.** In addition to being a shield, this item also counts as a weapon suitable for throwing, usable for any fighting style that does not have the **Exclusive** trait. You may apply weapon reforge traits and weapon aspects to this item.\n* **Steady (Resolute).** While you gain the benefits of the Raise Shield action or Reactive Block reaction using this item, you gain advantage on saving throws made to resist being disoriented.\n* **Cloaking.** When you take the Raise Shield action using this item, you become invisible until you are either hit with an attack or until you no longer benefit from the Raise Shield action.\n* **Solid.** While you gain the benefits of the Raise Shield action or Reactive Block reaction using this item, you gain advantage on saving throws made to resist becoming incapacitated, stunned, or frozen.\n\nOnce per long rest, after taking the Raise Shield action using this item, you may take a Use Item action to cause all creatures in a 10 foot cone originating in front of you to make a **Quick-Wits** saving throw. The DC of the saving throw depends on the rarity of this item (14 for Common, 17 for Uncommon, 20 for Rare, and 23 for Legendary). On a failure, a creature becomes unconscious without its **Prone** condition trait (they do not fall prone).","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"Raise Shield action","mainType":"Shield","subType":"","flavor":"An object conceived at the boundary between rest and dream, where the skewing of logic produces a barrier against all manner of attack and possibility.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":118000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"aBYbeQWeN3MoYyfW","name":"Ichorforged Maul","type":"curio","img":"icons/tools/smithing/hammer-maul-steel-grey.webp","system":{"description":"This weapon is purposed for the Heavy fighting style. This weapon has the following traits and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with minor reforge traits and up to two major reforge traits of your choice.\n\n* **Energized (Venomous).** When you hit with a weapon attack using this item, you may convert all of the attack's damage to **poison damage**.\n\n* **Specialized (Weighted).** Once per rest while equipped, you may negate the repetition penalty incurred when you perform **Wallop**.\n\n* **Keen.** The critical hit threshold of weapon attacks made with this item is reduced by 1\\.\n\n* **Obliterating.** While equipped, you gain advantage on Wreck an Object checks and attacks against objects using this item deal double damage.\n\nOnce per long rest, after you make a weapon attack with this item, you may take a Use Item action to cause the target of the attack to make a **Fortitude** saving throw to resist **poison damage**. On a failure, the target is poisoned for 10 minutes. A creature poisoned by this aspect may retry the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on a success. The saving throw's DC and the damage dealt is based on the item's rarity:\n\n* **Common**. DC 14 against **2d10 poison damage**.\n\n* **Uncommon**. DC 17 against **4d10 poison damage**.\n\n* **Rare**. DC 20 against **6d10 poison damage.**\n\n* **Legendary**. DC 23 against **8d10 poison damage.**","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Weapon","subType":"","flavor":"A foul monument of blasphemy dredged from the depths of the planarverse.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":119000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"dxA8iRUiJahOUb1K","name":"Stellar Mantle","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/chest/robe-collared-blue.webp","system":{"description":"This armor may be any type of armor. This armor has the following trait and aspect. When you purchase or craft this item, you may replace the traits with reforge traits of your choice of at most two major reforge traits.\n\nasdfas\n\n* **Resistant (Planelinked).** You gain a DB against **force** damage based on the rarity of the item: 5, 10, 15, and 20 for Common, Uncommon, Rare, and Legendary respectively.\n\n* **Shock-Absorbing.** When you are dealt falling damage, you may halve the damage taken.\n\n* **Adamantine.** Critical hits scored against you instead count as normal hits.\n\n* **Swift.** Your Speed is increased by 10 feet.\n\nAs a Use Item action, you may either **Point** or, once per long rest, **Guide**:\n\n* **Point.** You make a ranged special attack using your INT, WIS, or CHA against a target within 60 feet of you. On a hit, a target is *aligned* to you for 10 minutes and dealt **radiant damage** based on the item's rarity (2d6 for Common, 4d6 for Uncommon, 6d6 for Rare, and 8d6 for Legendary). A target of this attack may allow it to automatically hit and deal no damage.\n\n* **Guide.** You teleport all creatures and objects aligned by **Point** to unoccupied spaces within your Reach.","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Armor","subType":"","flavor":"A well-worn coat embroidered with starlight and fashioned with astral compasses. As nebulae and liquid worlds roil through the endless space of spaces, only a true north finds its way through.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":120000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"GtsOfFF5Qt2dWhuH","name":"Armor Reforge (Uncommon)","type":"curio","img":"icons/tools/smithing/plate-steel-grey.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Uncommon. You may add a minor armor reforge trait to it.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Common Armor","flavor":"Arduous effort is hammered into the plating, emboldening the magic within it.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":121000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"DX1TIxhf02i0Qxm7","name":"Shield Reforge (Uncommon)","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-steel-grey.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Uncommon. You may add a minor shield reforge trait to it.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Common Shield","flavor":"Polished to an immaculate shine.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":122000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Pf9GKADwaH3gufxP","name":"Weapon Reforge (Uncommon)","type":"curio","img":"icons/weapons/swords/shortsword-guard-steel-worn.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Uncommon. You may add a minor weapon reforge trait to it.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Common Weapon","flavor":"Folded, bright steel is honed to deadly precision.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":123000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"X7quM3e78mF5ULbh","name":"Armor Reforge (Rare)","type":"curio","img":"icons/tools/smithing/anvil.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Rare. You may add a minor or major armor reforge trait to it.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Uncommon Armor","flavor":"Everything from the fittings to the protective pieces are perfectly suited for its wearer.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":124000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"jZ55gTPyjXxUDSJx","name":"Shield Reforge (Rare)","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-embossed-gold.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Rare. You may add a minor or major shield reforge trait to it.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Uncommon Shield","flavor":"An emblem of a cause forged in the fires of passion.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":125000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"YDNOpts6kN6FFedM","name":"Weapon Reforge (Rare)","type":"curio","img":"icons/weapons/swords/greatsword-crossguard-embossed-gold.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Rare. You may add a minor or major weapon reforge trait to it.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Uncommon Weapon","flavor":"Hardest adamant with a razor edge.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":126000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"u2ClhZjzNtJe3Lxm","name":"Armor Reforge (Legendary)","type":"curio","img":"icons/skills/trades/smithing-anvil-silver-red.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Legendary. You may add a minor or major armor reforge trait to it.","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Rare Armor","flavor":"Tested through time and battle, the craftsmanship proves its own legacy.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":127000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"f5WjEwXuf8e7nUoM","name":"Shield Reforge (Legendary)","type":"curio","img":"icons/equipment/shield/kite-steel-boss-gold.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Legendary. You may add a minor or major shield reforge trait to it.","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Rare Shield","flavor":"An emblazoned crest is affixed, now inextricably linked with your name and legend.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":128000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"WIELoeMJvnUrfnmo","name":"Weapon Reforge (Legendary)","type":"curio","img":"icons/weapons/swords/greatsword-guard-gold.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Legendary. You may add a minor or major weapon reforge trait to it.\n\n*Minor Armor Reforge Trait*\n\nMultiple variants of **Mobile** exist as listed below. You gain a basic mobility as determined by one of the following variants:\n\n* **Finned.** You gain basic Swimming mobility.\n\n* **Springed.** You gain basic Jumping mobility.\n\n* **Stabilized.** You gain basic Climbing mobility.\n\n*Minor Armor Reforge Trait*\n\nMultiple variants of **Resistant** exist as listed below. You gain a DB based on the rarity of the item: 5, 10, 15, and 20 for Common, Uncommon, Rare, and Legendary respectively. The type of damage resisted by the DB is determined by one of the following variants:\n\n* **Neutralized.** The DB is against **acid damage**.\n\n* **Rimeweft.** The DB is against **cold damage**.\n\n* **Hearthwrought.** The DB is against **fire damage**.\n\n* **Planelinked.** The DB is against **force damage**.\n\n* **Grounded.** The DB is against **lightning damage**.\n\n* **Soulful.** The DB is against **necrotic damage**.\n\n* **Curative.** The DB is against **poison damage**.\n\n* **Judicious.** The DB is against **psychic damage**.\n\n* **Shimmering.** The DB is against **radiant damage**.\n\n*Minor Armor Reforge Trait*\n\nWhen you are dealt falling damage, you may halve the damage taken.\n\n*Minor Armor Reforge Trait*\n\nYou do not fall prone from burning a Resolve.\n\n*Major Armor Reforge Trait*\n\nCritical hits scored against you instead count as normal hits.\n\n*Major Armor Reforge Trait*\n\nYou cannot be pushed or pulled.\n\n*Major Armor Reforge Trait*\n\nWhile worn, your Speed is increased by 10 feet.","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Battlesmith","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Rare Weapon","flavor":"A name is etched into it, forged in battle and quenched in true purpose.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":129000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"CVVP2unSGYzUmelE","name":"Spell Scroll","type":"curio","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-bound-blue-white.webp","system":{"description":"This item can exist at multiple rarities. The Common/Uncommon/Rare/Legendary variants of this item have a crafting threshold score of 30/40/50/60 respectively, and other statistics shown below use this same notation.\n\nA spell of baseline Circle 1st/2nd/3rd/4th is *written* onto this item (when created from a stock recipe, the spell is chosen when the stock recipe's crafting project begins rather than when this item is produced). The written spell has one of the following limitations:\n\n* **If you craft this item**, the spell must be from one of the spell lists chosen for your Scrivener specialization.\n\n* **If you purchase this item**, the GM determines the available spell list(s) from which you are able to choose.\n\nAs a Use Item action, you may expend this item to cast the spell written on this item at 1st/2nd/3rd/4th Circle using your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier.","rarity":"Varies","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"Varies","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Consumable","subType":"Spell scroll","flavor":"I can be anything, take a look.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":130000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"tHIkXHBem3IJ6A7P","name":"Embalmed Eye","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/biological/eye-blue-gold.webp","system":{"description":"Once per long rest, you may recall a moment with perfect clarity that you had experienced an hour or more earlier but since the end of your last long rest. Until you dismiss this effect as an action, your senses are replaced with what you had at that moment. While in this state, you gain advantage on all INT and WIS effort and trade checks examining details in the recalled moment.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Life Ball**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"A perfectly preserved specimen complete with a frozen reflection of its last moment alive.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":131000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"9d9qgvOMVLvOsee1","name":"Mourning Crest","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/brooch-jeweled-pink.webp","system":{"description":"Once per rest, as a Use Item action, you may learn if there are any undead creatures within 60 feet of you.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Armor of Souls**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"A relic shedding tears of dew with each dawn of a new day. Those left behind remain closer still.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":132000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"5bwA5LfqXDZMRm8e","name":"Stardust Wand","type":"curio","img":"icons/weapons/wands/wand-star-white.webp","system":{"description":"You may cast **Sign** and produce its **Light** effect using your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Astral Darts**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"Carved from a tree that grew on an asteroid that fell to the earth, so the legend goes.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":133000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zeYCrKSHaEVjB4Ni","name":"Charcoal Whistle","type":"curio","img":"icons/tools/instruments/flute-simple-wood.webp","system":{"description":"As a Use Item action, you may cause a target within your Reach to be set ablaze.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Erupting Flame**\n\n* 2nd Circle: **Fireball**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"Brittle remains held in form by vivid memories of flame. In song, you revive that vigor.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":134000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"HN16fitj4b4rHb9t","name":"Loaded Die","type":"curio","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/dice-runed-brown.webp","system":{"description":"When your character rolls the **Loaded Die**, they may decide the outcome beforehand. Additionally, you may cast **Tricksleeve** using your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Bend Luck**\n\n* 2nd Circle: **Resistance**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"An anomalous six-sided die wrought from forces of improbability. The nature of luck itself seems to bend about its presence.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":135000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"4zJuELWC6a8NqUps","name":"Mist Seer's Journal","type":"curio","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-embossed-blue.webp","system":{"description":"You may cast **Spectral Lantern** using your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Fog Cloud**\n\n* 2nd Circle: **Lucidity**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"Countless expeditions and routes cover each page of the tome. What remains to be answered is where such a place could be found.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":136000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Ep5NNDWJRxP2o7Ek","name":"Clockwork Orb","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/materials/glass-orb-blue-gold.webp","system":{"description":"When you make an Analyze check, you may choose to gain advantage on the check. If you do, you do not learn any information from the Analyze check until the start of your next turn.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Animate Interceptor**\n\n* 2nd Circle: **Accelerate**\n\n* 3rd Circle: **Crystalline Sentinel**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Rarity","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"A glossy sphere acting as a window into an endless matrix of spinning cogs and wheels, slowly calculating a solution encoded in its concordant motions.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":137000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"bZKGuNqMHPNRUGhS","name":"Faeglass Shard","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/glass-crystal-green.webp","system":{"description":"Once per rest, as a Use Item action, you may cause a target creature within 30 feet of you to make a **Courage** saving throw against either DC 20 or your Spell DC for any of your Spellcasting or Battlecasting features, whichever is highest. On a failure, you may choose to either learn the target's greatest personal regret or their smallest combat check bonus (you learn multiple if there is a tie).\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Sanguine Sliver**\n\n* 2nd Circle: **Shatter**\n\n* 3rd Circle: **Imprisonment**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"Fragments of a broken mirror whisper with the remorseful wails of those trapped behind it.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":138000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"5BMm8H1m9Tf6QFkK","name":"Sand Bag","type":"curio","img":"icons/containers/bags/pouch-cloth-tan.webp","system":{"description":"This bag is enchanted to produce seemingly endless, magical sand. As a Use Item action, you may cover a target within your Reach with this sand. While covered in this manner, the target is under the effects of **Phosphorescence**. An action may be used to clean the sand off of the target and end the effect.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Drowsiness**\n\n* 2nd Circle: **Sleep**\n\n* 3rd Circle: **Enthralling Performance**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"Sleep with one eye open...","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":139000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"MPGQAUpQNNgYOA56","name":"Fenwretch Manuscript","type":"curio","img":"icons/sundries/books/book-embossed-roots-green.webp","system":{"description":"While equipped, you gain the following benefits:\n\n* You may cast **Antivenom** using your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier.\n\n* As an action, you may either become poisoned or cleanse yourself of being poisoned.\n\n* While you are poisoned or have that condition suppressed, you gain DB 20 against **biological damage** and once per turn, when you deal **poison damage** with a spell effect, you may add 10 to the damage roll.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Poison Needles**\n\n* 2nd Circle: **Toxic Fume**\n\n* 3rd Circle: **Polymorph**\n\n* 4th Circle: **Miasma**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"Held dearest by the most spiteful of cultivators. Endless hexes line the wilted margins.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":140000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"LxWgSYBmoFPhQrx7","name":"Gildroot Braid","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/materials/hair-braid-gold.webp","system":{"description":"You may cast **Bristle Lash** using your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier. When you do, you may cause the spell attack to automatically hit and convert all damage dealt to instead be **regained as ST**.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Earthen Wall**\n\n* 2nd Circle: **Circle of Renewal**\n\n* 3rd Circle: **Radiant Arsenal**\n\n* 4th Circle: **Violent Bloom**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"Glittering roots from the foundations of the world gnarled into a ring. Flecks of immaterial gold drift away from the wooden spirals as your spells pass through the center.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":141000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"LqBTDVJdu8JNuNT8","name":"Lightning Rod","type":"curio","img":"icons/commodities/tech/glass-electrode.webp","system":{"description":"While equipped, you gain the following benefits:\n\n* You may cast **Static Shock** using your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier.\n\n* If a target creature within 15 feet of you takes **lightning damage**, you may take a reaction to redirect the damage to you and this item's aspect regains a Spell Charge for every 15 damage taken this way.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, you may cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: **Lightning Bolt**\n\n* 2nd Circle: **Electric Tomb**\n\n* 3rd Circle: **Squall**\n\n* 4th Circle: **Warp Cage**\n\nWhen you complete a long rest, all expended Spell Charges imbued into the item are restored.","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Spellcasting Focus","subType":"","flavor":"The first mage to use this item found the results quite...shocking.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":142000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hGJ6MyEUHqTQPbVd","name":"Custom Focus","type":"curio","img":"icons/magic/holy/meditation-chi-focus-blue.webp","system":{"description":"You upgrade the rarity of a Mundane spellcasting focus to Common, choose a 1st Circle spell, and grant it the following aspect (the item is now able to accept aspects). The chosen spell has one of the following limitations:\n\n* **If you craft this upgrade**, the spell must be from one of the spell lists chosen for your Scrivener specialization.\n\n* **If you purchase this upgrade**, the GM determines the available spell list(s) from which you are able to choose.\n\nThis item is imbued with a certain number of *Spell Charges* depending on its rarity (1 for Common, 2 for Uncommon, 3 for Rare, and 4 for Legendary). As a Use Item action, this item can cast and heighten the spells from the list below by expending a number of Spell Charges equal to the Circle of spell cast. You may use your INT, WIS, or CHA as your spellcasting modifier when casting these spells:\n\n* 1st Circle: (The spell chosen as part of **Custom Focus**)","rarity":"Common","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"30","actionType":"Use Item action","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Mundane spellcasting focus","flavor":"There is nothing before a beginning and everything follows from there.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":143000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"yHrVQd9tIWvI5JHq","name":"Focus Infusion (Uncommon)","type":"curio","img":"icons/weapons/wands/wand-gem-blue.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Uncommon. If the item has an **Imbued Spells** aspect, you may add a 2nd Circle spell of your choosing to its list of spells. The chosen spell has one of the following limitations:\n\n* **If you craft this upgrade**, the spell must be from one of the spell lists chosen for your Scrivener specialization.\n\n* **If you purchase this upgrade**, the GM determines the available spell list(s) from which you are able to choose.","rarity":"Uncommon","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"40","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Common Spellcasting focus","flavor":"Rough drafts are what they are.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":144000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"OaVetQwPRqHj4HWg","name":"Focus Infusion (Rare)","type":"curio","img":"icons/weapons/wands/wand-gem-purple.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Rare. If the item has an **Imbued Spells** aspect, you may add a 3rd Circle spell of your choosing to its list of spells. The chosen spell has one of the following limitations:\n\n* **If you craft this upgrade**, the spell must be from one of the spell lists chosen for your Scrivener specialization.\n\n* **If you purchase this upgrade**, the GM determines the available spell list(s) from which you are able to choose.","rarity":"Rare","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"50","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Uncommon Spellcasting focus","flavor":"From a wider perspective, you can see how it could all be better composed.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":145000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"nGH060p7xVHrskDF","name":"Focus Infusion (Legendary)","type":"curio","img":"icons/weapons/wands/wand-star-gold.webp","system":{"description":"The item's rarity is upgraded to Legendary. If the item has an **Imbued Spells** aspect, you may add a 4th Circle spell of your choosing to its list of spells. The chosen spell has one of the following limitations:\n\n* **If you craft this upgrade**, the spell must be from one of the spell lists chosen for your Scrivener specialization.\n\n* **If you purchase this upgrade**, the GM determines the available spell list(s) from which you are able to choose.","rarity":"Legendary","discipline":"Scrivener","craftingThresholdScore":"60","actionType":"Passive","mainType":"Upgrade","subType":"Rare Spellcasting focus","flavor":"Perfected down to the letter, diacritics and all.","quantity":1,"weight":0},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":146000,"ownership":{"default":0},"permission":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
